{"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pause"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"modules":[{"name":"UltraliteSDK"}],"title":"pause()","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:12UltraliteSDK12ScrollLayoutC12AutoScrollerC5pauseyyF"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","doc:\/\/com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout","doc:\/\/com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/pause()"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/pause()"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pause"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}]}],"kind":"declarations"}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"pause the scrolling text"}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"AutoScroller is a utility class to send a large known block of predfined text to the glasses to be smoothly scrolled."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is simlar to what is seen on a teleprompter or in movie credits.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This class was written using the "},{"code":"ScrollLayout","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" commands and is nothing more than a convience class."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Everything used this class can be written from the public SDK."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It scrolls the text much like a teleprompter would with basic commands to pause and resume the scrolling."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The duration (speed) of the scrolling can be modified while scrolling by seting the ","type":"text"},{"code":"duration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It can support any language that the font supports."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If the content is not known up front, or subject to change, this is the utility class will not work (use ","type":"text"},{"code":"LiveText","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance instead)."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller","title":"ScrollLayout.AutoScroller","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol"},"doc://com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout","title":"ScrollLayout","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ScrollLayout"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"When Ultralite.requestControl with a .scroll layout type .. this is the class you interate with to draw scrolling text to the screen.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Once the layout is .scrolled you must send one configure message to tell the layout how to setup.  It will setup the slice height and how many slices are visible.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"There are two supported modes: autoScroll on\/off"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"When autoScroll is true, the slices are automatically scrolled.  Subscribe to the delgate and listen for the scrolled callback, when you get it send another slice of text","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is false, you can drive the slices and how they look on the screen.  You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time."}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK":{"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk","kind":"symbol","title":"UltraliteSDK","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this SDK to easily send text and images to your Vuxix smart glasses."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","type":"topic","role":"collection"},"doc://com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller/pause()":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"pause the scrolling text"}],"title":"pause()","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.vuzix.UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/pause()","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/pause()","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pause"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol"}}}